<h2>Rhode Island Incentives & Rebates</h2>
<p>Rhode Island offers some of the most comprehensive renewable energy incentives in New England, making solar and HVAC investments highly attractive for homeowners. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) remains the cornerstone incentive, allowing homeowners to deduct 30% of their total solar installation costs from their federal taxes through 2032, after which it steps down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. This credit applies to all system components including panels, inverters, mounting equipment, and installation labor, with no cap on the credit amount.</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Federal Solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC):</strong> 30% of total system cost through 2032, covering equipment and installation. The credit can be carried forward if it exceeds tax liability in the installation year, and there are no income restrictions or system size limits.</li>

<li><strong>Renewable Energy Growth (REG) Program:</strong> Rhode Island's signature solar incentive provides 15-20 year performance-based payments for solar energy production. Small-scale residential systems (‚â§25kW) receive premium rates ranging from \$0.285-\$0.385 per kWh produced, significantly above standard electricity rates.</li>

<li><strong>National Grid ConnectedSolutions:</strong> This demand response program pays solar customers with battery storage \$150-225 per kW annually for allowing the utility to discharge stored energy during peak demand periods, typically 50-60 hours per year during summer afternoons.</li>

<li><strong>Property Tax Exemption:</strong> Solar installations are exempt from local property tax assessments, meaning the added home value from solar doesn't increase property taxes. This exemption applies for 20 years from installation date.</li>

<li><strong>HVAC Rebates through National Grid:</strong> Energy efficiency rebates include up to \$750 for ENERGY STAR heat pumps, \$400 for high-efficiency central AC units, and \$100-150 for smart thermostats. Heat pump water heater rebates provide up to \$750 additional savings.</li>
</ul>

<p>To maximize incentives, homeowners should work with certified installers familiar with Rhode Island's programs and ensure all equipment meets program requirements. The REG program has annual enrollment caps, making early application important for securing the highest incentive rates.</p>

